Port Elizabeth-based Luvo Manyonga has broken the African indoor long jump record leaping to a mark of 8.40m at a meeting in Metz, France, on Sunday night. He beat the previous mark of 8.36m set by Ghana’s Ignisious Gaisah in 2006. Port Elizabeth-based long jump superstar Luvo Manyonga will be looking to start the year on a high note at the Paris Indoor Meeting at the Accor Hotel Arena tonight. The 27-year-old arrived in France on Sunday for a whistle-stop tour and will compete in a two-legged series before returning to… February 7, 2018 Port Elizabeth-based world champion Luvo Manyonga soared to a world-leading distance of 8.32 metres in the men's long jump at Wednesday's indoor athletics meeting in Paris. It was a first career indoor appearance for Manyonga, an Olympic silver medallist at Rio 2016, as he targets more silverware at next month's… February 8, 2018 ALL eyes will be on world champion Wayde van Niekerk, who leads a full-strength South African onslaught tonight as he makes his international season debut at the IAAF Diamond League meeting in Rome. Van Niekerk clocked 44.11sec at the ASA Open Championships in Bloemfontein last month and is the fastest… June 2, 2016